&quot; at Museum of Modern Art on May 16, 2023 in New York City. Credit: Taylor Hill/GETTY" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Sidney-Sweeney-Posing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Sidney-Sweeney-Posing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Sidney-Sweeney-Posing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Sidney-Sweeney-Posing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Sidney-Sweeney-Posing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Sidney-Sweeney-Posing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Sydney Sweeney has defended <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/euphoria"><em>Euphoria</em></a> director Sam Levinson over the show&#39;s sexually explicit scenes.</p><p> <em>Euphoria</em> has won nine Emmys – two of them for its lead, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/zendaya">Zendaya</a> – and has made Sweeney a star. But its depiction of sex in a show about high schoolers has turned Levinson into a controversial figure. Meanwhile, his latest <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/hbo">HBO</a> series <em>The Idol</em> has brought about similar criticism.</p><p> However, in a new interview with <a href="https://variety.com/2023/tv/features/sydney-sweeney-not-typecast-cassie-reality-white-lotus-interview-1235688915/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Variety</em></a> , Sweeney defended the director, claiming she feels “free and confident” in her <em>Euphoria</em> role of Cassie Howard.</p><p> “You have me, you have Z, you have all of these very strong-minded, independent women. If we didn&#39;t feel comfortable with something, or we saw something we didn&#39;t like, we&#39;d all speak up,” she said.</p><p> “It&#39;s hard to see someone completely trashed by the public and the media when no one&#39;s actually there. We are there, and clearly we&#39;re still working on the show, and we&#39;re still supportive.” </p><figure id="attachment_3213060" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3213060" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3213060" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Sam-Levinson-main-new.jpg" alt="Sam Levinson" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Sam-Levinson-main-new.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Sam-Levinson-main-new-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Sam-Levinson-main-new-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Sam-Levinson-main-new-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Sam-Levinson-main-new-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Sam-Levinson-main-new-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3213060" class="wp-caption-text"> Sam Levinson CREDIT: Jeff Kravitz/FilmMagic for HBO</figcaption></figure><p> Sweeney added of <em>Euphoria</em> : “The point is making people uncomfortable, and thinking outside the box. What else is the point of art?” Sweeney says. “For me, I feel so free and confident now. And I&#39;ve found that through Cassie.”</p><p> Elsewhere, Sweeney previously revealed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/sydney-sweeney-reveals-her-family-members-walked-out-on-euphoria-3451836">two of her family members walked out of the room while watching her in <em>Euphoria</em></a> .</p><p> “My mum visited me on set at the time, so she like knew the story and I talked to her a lot about it – my dad didn&#39;t,” she said. “I didn&#39;t prepare my dad at all.”</p><p> According to the actress, her father decided to watch the series with her grandparents without telling her first. Unaware of the nature of show, which follows a group of high school students as they struggle with issues of drugs, sex and violence, Sweeney revealed: “My dad and my grandpa turned it off and walked out.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/sydney-sweeney-defends-euphoria-director-sam-levinson-over-sexually-explicit-scenes-3481099">Sydney Sweeney defends &#39;Euphoria&#39; director Sam Levinson over sexually explicit scenes</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
